<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/849> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #849" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Delivered the persons who had pledged peace at Caudium to the Samnites (Liv. 9.10.8-10, and 11.9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/822> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #822" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.38-40; cf. Zon. 7.26. Credited with an important victory and a triumph by Livy's main source, but in others (followed by Act. Tr.), appointed to carry on the Ludi Romani owing to the illness of the Praetor (Liv. 8.40.1-5). See above, Consuls, and Degrassi 108, 415." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/775> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #775" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.17.5; Diod. 17.62.1; Chr. 354 (Calvino et Arvinas II); Fast. Hyd. (Galbino et Cosso); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 107, 412f. Peace with Alexander of Epirus (Cassiod.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/774> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #774" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Cossus, see Act. Tr. on 343; for the filiation of Domitius, ee Fast. Cap. on 280." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/721> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #721" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Div. 1.51; Liv. 7.28.10; 10.31.10; Diod. 16.77.1; Act. Tr.; Plin. NH 16.11; App. Samn. 1; Auct. Vir. Ill. 26; Chr. 354 (Corvo III et Cosso III); Fast. Hyd. (Corvino III et Cosco), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 106, 408f. At Saticula in the First Samnite War Cornelius was saved from a dangerous position by Decius Mus (see Tribunes of the Soldiers), and thereafter won a victory and celebrated a triumph (Liv. 7.32.2, 34-37.3, and 38.3; Cic. Div. 1.51; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 541; Frontin. Str. 1.5.14; 4.5.9; Auct. Vir. Ill. 26). Valerius was victorious at Mt. Gaurus and Suessula, celebrated a triumph, and returned to protect Campania during the winter (Liv. 7.32-33, and 37.4-38; Dion. Hal. 15.3; Act. Tr., Degrassi 68f., 541; App. Samn. 1; Auct. Vir. Ill. 26). On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 49, no. 49." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/699> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #699" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.26.12; Fast. Cap. See Degrassi 34f., 106, 406f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/671> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #671" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.19.10. See Degrassi 105, 404f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/670> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #670" ;
